I Completed #75hard for the second time(on the right). The first time I completed #75hardprogram it changed my life in 2019 (on the left). The reason why I started again was because I was negotiating with myself. Discipline and mental toughness will disappear if they’re not applied daily. I wasn’t holding myself to the highest standard. I let myself get too comfortable. I’ve known for a long time that doing #75hard would solve majority of the things I was struggling with however I was too afraid to commit. I wasn’t willing to bet on myself for 75 days. I can confidently say that I pushed this off for way too long! @andyfrisella thank you for leading by example. Don’t be afraid to bet on yourself. Take action on the things that are going to get you 1% closer to your goals.

1% better with @lskd . In 2018 I decided to make the choice to grow 1% better every single day. This has been a primary focus in my life in multiple different areas including my fitness, business, and relationships. There have been times when I felt like throwing in the towel and quitting but my mind always goes back to the saying “Just 1% more.” The goals we set for ourselves can seem so far. If we focus on moving 1% closer each day by the end of the year we are 365% closer than we were a year ago. Identify and set the standard for yourself! 

Thank you @benskriloff for working your magic on this video

Video editing is the most time-consuming part of the creative process. I’ve been editing videos for the past seven years and from my experience there are two essential people that entrepreneurs and brands must have a part of their business, and if you’re lucky you will be able to find one person that has the skill set to be equivalent to these two hires. The first person is a video editor. The video editor is going to have the expertise to guide you in the creation process and bring your vision to life. The second key player is someone to support on ideation and strategy. They need to be able to look at your story and create a clear roadmap on how your story will be integrated into the content. Their primary job is to lead the editor.
